Rating: 0
I turn this dish into a main course by browning 4 chicken thighs in olive oil, then cooking them in the stock with some rosemary and thyme sprigs. I then stain the stock to be added back in later, and when the chicken has cooled, remove the meat and discard the skin and bones. During the last 15 minutes of cooking time which, I think is better at 45 minutes, I add the chicken meat. Delicious one pot meal. A sqeeze of lemon to serve really livens it up.

Rating: 4
love this recipe... i agree with the previous reviewers - 1,500 mL is more than enough liquid. I added 4 diced cloves fresh garlic as well as some indian spice (roughly 1 tsp each of ground cumin, tumeric and a home made masala mix and a about 1/3 tsp cayenne pepper) in the first stage... and mixed in handfuls of roughly chopped fresh parsley and arugula just prior to serving and while the lentils were warm enough to get the greens to wilt. i crumbled some good goat's milk feta overtop and with toasted pita... and found we had a complete, light meal and super delicious meal.

